    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced chicken thigh </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it all together until fully coated</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>spiced chicken thigh</strong></p>",
